2026-05-06 16:15:06,904 INFO Ground truth: The Chief Justice argued that true liberty of the press meant freedom from prior licensing or restraint, not freedom from punishment after publication. He stated that every man who prints does so at his peril, just as every man who speaks does so at his peril. He argued that restraining the press through punishment of libels was actually necessary to preserve liberty, and that tolerating licentious abuse of government was the most likely way to destroy freedom.
